The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for creating artistic imagery, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses various approaches and evaluation methods for improving the original Neural Style Transfer (NST) algorithm, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the applications of NST in various fields, including graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
